OL,3,C'Coronation Street storyline made me
OL,4,Cseek help from abusive partner'
OL,6,FSpeaking to ITV Tyne Tees as rates of
OL,7,Fdomestic abuse-related offences rise
OL,8,Facross the North East, the mum said
OL,9,Fshe did not report her abusive partner
OL,10,Fto the police as her self-confidence
OL,11,Fhad been "destroyed".
OL,13,F"I was told where I could go, who I
OL,14,Fcould see," she explained. "In the
OL,15,Fend, I couldn't go out. (My partner)
OL,16,Fwas trying to cause arguments in front
OL,17,Fof our child.
OL,19,F"On the surface, he was a gentleman, a
OL,20,Fgood job, family orientated. But the
OL,21,Fabuse was exhausting"
